 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.505","title":"[audit][messaging] Restore explicit operator-intent workload class compilation","description":"Bounded audit/fix in src/messaging/policy.rs: OperatorIntentCompiler exposes semantic service classes in policy/degradation logic that are not reachable from OperatorIntent. Add an explicit workload-shape signal so read-model, low-value fanout, and expensive-replay classes can actually be compiled, then cover with focused tests.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-01T17:21:29.945430951Z","created_by":"SnowyOsprey","updated_at":"2026-04-01T17:30:17.792315438Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","messaging"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.505","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-01T17:21:29.945430951Z","created_by":"SnowyOsprey","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2854,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.505","author":"SnowyOsprey","text":"Working src/messaging/policy.rs and src/messaging/mod.rs. Found that OperatorIntentCompiler only emitted four of eight semantic service classes; patch adds explicit OperatorWorkloadShape input, wires compile_service_class to respect it after reply/lease precedence, and adds focused regressions for read-model, low-value fanout, and expensive-replay lanes. Agent Mail reservation/inbox calls are still hitting transient DB errors, so bead comments are the durable coordination path for now.","created_at":"2026-04-01T17:25:16Z"},{"id":2857,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.505","author":"SnowyOsprey","text":"Implemented the audit fix in src/messaging/policy.rs and src/messaging/mod.rs. Added public OperatorWorkloadShape to OperatorIntent so OperatorIntentCompiler can actually emit ReadModel, LowValueFanout, and ExpensiveReplay instead of only four reachable SemanticServiceClass variants; compile_service_class now honors explicit workload shape after lease-repair/reply-critical precedence, and inline regressions cover the three newly reachable lanes plus round-trip serialization. Static validation: rustfmt +nightly --edition 2024 --check src/messaging/policy.rs src/messaging/mod.rs passed; git diff --check on both files passed. Cargo validation remains blocked by the required offload path: rch exec keeps failing open with 'all workers failed preflight checks'. Non-destructive diagnosis found this worktree is 84G and .beads alone is 17G, with multi-GB WAL snapshot files under .beads*; this likely explains worker preflight rejection under current disk-pressure rules. I did not run local cargo as final validation because AGENTS.md requires offloading.","created_at":"2026-04-01T17:30:17Z"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.506","title":"[audit][tracing] Fix underscore-bound tracing bindings in feature-enabled/clippy paths","description":"Fresh-eyes child under asupersync-1qfd0. Audit found a bounded compile-surface bug class under `tracing-integration`: several files bind underscore-prefixed locals to silence unused-variable warnings when tracing is disabled, then reference the non-underscored name inside `tracing::*` macros. This leaves feature-enabled builds broken. Fix the affected sites in `src/runtime/waker.rs`, `src/decoding.rs`, `src/distributed/recovery.rs`, `src/web/middleware.rs`, and `src/messaging/jetstream.rs`, add focused regression coverage where it strengthens the contract, and validate with rch-backed feature-enabled check/clippy plus fmt check.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"FuchsiaCitadel","created_at":"2026-04-01T17:21:43.926371193Z","created_by":"Codex","updated_at":"2026-04-01T17:45:01.682561328Z","closed_at":"2026-04-01T17:45:01.682210476Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","feature-enabled","runtime","tracing","waker"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.506","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-01T17:21:43.926371193Z","created_by":"Codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2855,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.506","author":"Codex","text":"Progress 2026-04-01: confirmed the bug in src/runtime/waker.rs at lines 95-103, where WakeSource label binding drifted (`_source_label` vs `source_label`) and only stayed latent when tracing was compiled out. Patched the file by moving label mapping onto `WakeSource::label()` and added `wake_source_labels_are_stable` to pin the string contract. Validation launched through `rch exec -- ...`; remote workers failed preflight so rch fell back to local cargo, and the feature-enabled test/check/clippy lanes are currently queued behind shared package/build locks from concurrent agents. `rch exec -- cargo fmt --check` completed cleanly.","created_at":"2026-04-01T17:25:22Z"},{"id":2859,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.506","author":"FuchsiaCitadel","text":"2026-04-01 progress: completed the remaining non-tracing cleanup in src/messaging/jetstream.rs so the feature-enabled underscore-typo fix does not regress the tracing-disabled build. Existing patch set across src/runtime/waker.rs, src/decoding.rs, src/distributed/recovery.rs, src/web/middleware.rs, and src/messaging/jetstream.rs is now under fresh rch-backed feature-enabled validation. Agent Mail inbox/listing is still failing with a DB error from this host, so bead comments remain the durable coordination channel.","created_at":"2026-04-01T17:39:28Z"},{"id":2864,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.506","author":"FuchsiaCitadel","text":"2026-04-01 validation note: code patch set is complete for the bounded tracing compile-surface bug across runtime/waker, decoding, distributed/recovery, web/middleware, and messaging/jetstream. `cargo fmt --check` passed through rch; fresh feature-enabled cargo check/clippy retries are currently blocked because rch keeps failing open to local fallback on new jobs from this host, and those local fallbacks were killed immediately to honor the offload-only rule.","created_at":"2026-04-01T17:44:46Z"},{"id":2865,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.506","author":"Codex","text":"Completed 2026-04-01. Fixed the underscore-bound tracing binding bug class in src/runtime/waker.rs, src/decoding.rs, src/distributed/recovery.rs, src/web/middleware.rs, src/messaging/jetstream.rs, and follow-on clippy blockers in src/lab/runtime.rs and src/plan/fixtures.rs. Added wake_source_labels_are_stable in src/runtime/waker.rs to pin the label contract. Validation was run via rch exec with isolated cargo dirs: cargo fmt --check, cargo check -p asupersync --lib --features tracing-integration, cargo test -p asupersync --lib wake_source_labels_are_stable --features tracing-integration -- --nocapture, and cargo clippy -p asupersync --lib --features tracing-integration -- -D warnings all passed. Note: rch remote workers failed preflight and fell back to local cargo. MCP Agent Mail remains unusable in this session: health_check is green but register/list/fetch all still return transient database errors.","created_at":"2026-04-01T17:44:57Z"}]}
